  "prompt": "What is exactly is digital marketing?",
  "response": "Digital marketing is the practice of promoting products, services, or brands using digital technologies and channels to reach and engage potential customers. It encompasses a wide range of online marketing strategies and tactics, including:\n\n1. Search Engine Optimization (SEO)\n- Improving website visibility in search engine results\n\n2. Content Marketing\n- Creating and sharing valuable online content\n- Blogs, videos, podcasts, infographics\n\n3. Social Media Marketing\n- Promoting brands on platforms like Facebook, Instagram, Twitter\n- Engaging with audiences through social channels\n\n4. Email Marketing\n- Sending targeted emails to potential and existing customers\n- Newsletters, promotional campaigns\n\n5. Pay-Per-Click (PPC) Advertising\n- Paid ads on search engines and social media\n- Google Ads, Facebook Ads\n\n6. Affiliate Marketing\n- Promoting products through third-party websites\n- Earning commission for sales generated\n\n7. Influencer Marketing\n- Partnering with online personalities to promote products\n- Leveraging their audience and credibility\n\n8. Mobile Marketing\n- Targeting users on smartphones and tablets\n- Mobile-friendly websites, apps, SMS marketing\n\n9. Video Marketing\n- Creating promotional videos\n- YouTube advertising, video content\n\nThe goal of digital marketing is to reach target audiences effectively, increase brand awareness, drive website traffic, and ultimately generate leads and sales using digital platforms and technologies.",
